post_text:
Beginning Tuesday, March 24, 2020 meals will be provided to those 18 and under at three (3) different school sites from 8 a.m. - 11 a.m. The following school sites have been selected:

Ellington Elementary School

Teague Elementary School

Central Elementary School

The school district will provide curbside service at these sites from 8:00 a.m. to 11:00 a.m. for combination breakfast & lunch. Children should be present to receive a meal and only one meal per child will be provided.

We will provide “Grab and Go” meals only. Since we are only providing curbside service, a staff member will be available to hand your child their meal while you are still in your car.

Furthermore, WPS will run vans/suburbans to additional locations for meal pick up by students. These meals will also be “Grab and Go” as well. We will be at the following locations from 8:30 - 11:00 a.m.

Toppers Fire Department parking lot

Whitehorn Cove Fire and Rescue parking lot

White building 200 feet east of Ginny’s Log Cabin Grocery on 690 Road

Elk’s Lodge located at 33604 Longbay Road in the parking lot

Today the State Department of Education mandated all schools close and terminate all activities until April 6.

Tomorrow we plan to listen to a webcast from the SDE to gain guidance in the coming weeks on food, education expectations, who can work at school, etc. Although you may have questions, please give us a couple days to get a plan in place that keeps our students and staff safe while also providing students with any services that are permitted.

post_text:
Dear Parents -

Today we met with local county health department officials and several school district leaders in an effort to remain informed on the Coronavirus and its effect on our schools. What we learned today is that as of now we have no reason to close down our schools. However, this is a very fluid situation and the Center for Disease Control (CDC) is gathering data on an hourly basis from around the country and the state. Should we have a situation arise where we must close due to the Coronavirus we would consider transitioning to an online platform or allow for students to receive weekly educational packets. Currently there is no indication we need to pursue this form of education. We will remain informed by local health officials and the State Dept of Education on any future decisions.

Let me encourage you to make sure your students exercise proper hygiene practices and investigate the locations of your visit before you travel.

Have a fun and/or relaxing Spring Break!

Bulldog Strong,



Randy Harris

Superintendent

Wagoner Public Schools

918-485-4046

post_text:
Parents/Guardians
RAND is a research organization based in California. They are doing a nationwide study on the effects of a 4 Day School Week on public schools. We were selected to be a part of their research by participating in their survey. I encourage you and your student(s) to participate in their survey to assist with their research. We have data to show the 4 Day Week hasn't harmed Wagoner students. I hope their research will support our evidence. I believe that when a 4 Day Week is implemented with intentionality and purpose, it benefit students.
If you have any questions about the survey, please contact your student's school.

Wagoner public schools is sad to announce Tony Garrison, our custodian at Ellington School passed away yesterday. His funeral services will be Thursday at 3 pm. To honor Tony's impact on our staff and students from his many years of selfless service we will dismiss all schools Thursday at 2 pm.
Please lift up his family and friends in your thoughts and prayers.

Again, we will be dismissing school Thursday, October 24th at 2 pm. Buses will run at 2 pm as well.

If you have any additional questions or concerns feel free to contact our administration office, 9184854046

post_text:
We are going to tweak things just a little bit. I will delete the previous post so there is less confusion. Most of the same rules apply except we are separating middle school and high school routes. You can still react with a 😡 but please refrain from responding with 🤬.

1 - Green route is for high school. Please notice the one way portion of your route. (Where the SORRY is.)

2 - Blue route is for middle school.

3 - Please don't try and "cheat" by parking and calling the school to check your student out so they can walk to you. 🤔

4 - the places in red are still closed.

5 - middle school car drop off and pick up will be in the high school cafeteria parking lot.

6 - road repairs should be completed by next Tuesday.

7 - please set your DVRs to record your favorite shows due to extended time restraints for pick up and drop off.

8 - Thank you Mr. Moto 🤔 for pointing out where ms and hs cross paths. 😉

9 - please share the heck out of this post!

shared_text:
Wagoner Middle School
August 1, 2019 at 9:12 PM ·

T-minus 2 weeks and counting for school to start! Please refer to this screenshot for Open House times held 2 days prior.

Remember, ALL students must have up to date shot records and any student specifically entering the 7th grade MUST HAVE the T-dap immunization on their shot records or will not be allowed to enroll.

Also, the times listed for each grade will be strictly followed. If you have students in multiple grades at the middle school, come at a time that will span both time periods. WMS is open both before and after other buildings so please honor these times for each grade.
Thanks, and we'll see you then!
text:
**ATTENTION PARENTS**

Wagoner Middle School
August 1, 2019 at 9:12 PM ·

T-minus 2 weeks and counting for school to start! Please refer to this screenshot for Open House times held 2 days prior.

Remember, ALL students must have up to date shot records and any student specifically entering the 7th grade MUST HAVE the T-dap immunization on their shot records or will not be allowed to enroll.

Also, the times listed for each grade will be strictly followed. If you have students in multiple grades at the middle school, come at a time that will span both time periods. WMS is open both before and after other buildings so please honor these times for each grade.
Thanks, and we'll see you then!

Parents, your summer waiting is almost over!
🤔🤣

WMS open house will be Tuesday, August 7th from *4:30 to 7 p.m. Bring your student(s) and tour the building, pick up schedules, meet teachers, get a locker, and take tons of pics to post!

See you in less than a month!

post_text:
Let’s be clear, Wagoner Board of Education and administrators support our teachers. Like our teachers, we too support more funding for public education. The only thing we temporarily differed on is our paths for advocacy. If there were one clear path, wouldn’t we all choose it? Politics can be both unpredictable and volatile.
Ultimately, We have concluded supporting our teachers supersedes politics.
Therefore we will be allowing teachers to continue their advocacy at the capitol. This is a fluid situation so we will announce school closure on a daily basis.
As we have seen, our teachers are emphatic in their demands and we support their efforts.

The Wagoner Athletic Hall of Fame would like to announce that it’s inaugural Induction Ceremony will be held on March 31st, 2018, at 6pm. The ceremony will take place in the Hughes Event Center and there will be a reception for the inductees at 5:30pm. The cost to attend the event is $15 and that will include a catered meal from Smokin’ Sisters. Tickets can be purchased through the Wagoner Athletic office, C&H Sports, or Oklahoma Graphx. We want to invite all of you to join us as we recognize these Bulldog Legends!

Please join us in congratulating two outstanding WHS Seniors! Lauren Frost and Austin Condict both received a call from Northeastern State University's President Dr. Steve Turner this past weekend notifying them of their acceptance into the President's Leadership Class Scholarship Program at NSU. Both students were chosen based on their strong academic record and outstanding leadership abilities following a rigorous interview process. We have no doubt Austin and Lauren both have a bright future at NSU!

Wagoner High School
March 7, 2018 at 3:00 AM ·

Congratulations to our own Co-Valedictorian Kelsey Moore who is one of only five students to receive the Academic Scholars Scholarship totaling $45,000.00 at Northeastern State University! Kelsey is an exceptional student with plans to pursue a degree in education. Kelsey has also been named an Academic All-State recipient by the Oklahoma Foundation for Excellence. This honor is only bestowed on 100 exceptional seniors each year in the state of Oklahoma! Congratulations Kelsey! We cannot wait to see your future success!

The Wagoner Marching Band will compete at the OBA state marching competition October 14th in Yukon, Oklahoma. The band will be performing at 11:45 a.m. on Saturday. Awards will be handed out at 4:15 at which time we will know if the band will play in the finals.

WHS marching band has had a successful marching season. The Revolution routine has landed the band in the finals at each marching competition and we hope to end the year with another opportunity to make the finals in Yukon. Please come out and support the bulldog band!

post_text:
COMMUNITY OF WAGONER -

The Wagoner Bulldog Marching Band not only helps cheer the football team on every Friday night, they also compete in marching band competitions. Bulldog Marching Band will compete in several upcoming competitions, and your support at any or all of these events would be greatly appreciated! Saturday, September 23 will be the first competition of the year at the Oologah football stadium. The Wagoner Band will perform at 1:15, after which they will receive a score that will determine their standing in the finals later that night. One of the things the judges will be looking for during the performance is audience reaction, so the number of fans watching and their noise level can make a difference. Please come out and support your Wagoner Bulldog Marching Band and cheer them on to a successful marching band season. (You can find out about upcoming events by following the Wagoner Band Facebook page.)

Dates for band competitions:

September 23- Oologah, OK (1:15)

September 30 – Okmulgee, OK

October 5-Verdigris, OK

October 7- Bixby, OK

October 14- Mustang, OK

shared_text:
Wagoner High School
July 6, 2017 at 6:19 PM ·

SCHEDULE PICK-UP!!!

Schedule pick-up for the 17-18 school year will be as follows:

10th, 11th, and 12th grade will be Thursday, August 10th from 3:30-8:30 pm*.

Freshman Friday will be on Friday, August 11th from 3:30-8:30 pm*. All Incoming Freshmen and Freshmen Parents are encouraged to attend.

We will continue the tradition of our Pool Party for our Freshmen from 6:30-8:30 at the city pool. Pizza and drinks will be provided. The pool party event is for first year freshmen students only. Parents, siblings, older and younger friends will not be allowed to attend.

*PARENTS MUST ATTEND SCHEDULE PICK UP FOR ALL STUDENTS TO RECIEVE THEIR SCHEDULES.
Also, if your student owes a fine in the Media Center or for lost/damaged books or for lost athletic apparel it must be paid for in order to receive your schedule.

We hope you are having a fantastic and safe summer and look forward to seeing you in August!

post_text:
A special CONGRATULATIONS to our girls tennis team!
Girls Tennis played Regionals on May 1, 2017 at Henryetta . We pre-qualified 5 girls to attend Regionals and All 5 have qualified for State ! OKC Tennis Center May 5th & 6th . #1 Singles is Katy Roberts (first Singles player in Wagoner History to Qualify for State) #1 Doubles Alyssa Armstrong / Morgan Randolph (Morgan returning for her 3 year , made history last year with her doubles partner Kenzie Davis in getting on the podium as a Medalist at State) #2 Doubles Shelby Nolan and Madyson Robertson. Please Congratulate these young ladies for their hard work!
text:
A special CONGRATULATIONS to our girls tennis team!
Girls Tennis played Regionals on May 1, 2017 at Henryetta . We pre-qualified 5 girls to attend Regionals and All 5 have qualified for State ! OKC Tennis Center May 5th & 6th . #1 Singles is Katy Roberts (first Singles player in Wagoner History to Qualify for State) #1 Doubles Alyssa Armstrong / Morgan Randolph (Morgan returning for her 3 year , made history last year with her doubles partner Kenzie Davis in getting on the podium as a Medalist at State) #2 Doubles Shelby Nolan and Madyson Robertson. Please Congratulate these young ladies for their hard work!

March 30, 2017 at 3:18 PM ·

Drivers Ed sign-ups will begin on Wednesday, April 5th at 7:30 am in Ladonna Jeffers office. Classes are $150.00 and must be paid in order to reserve your spot.

All students are required to take 30 hours of classroom instruction and six hour of driving instruction. The classroom session will be held in the HS Media Center from 8:00 am - 6:00 pm, Monday, May 22nd - Wednesday, May 24th. Driving schedules will be passed out during the classroom instruction. They will schedule your child around vacation, camp, etc.

There are only 54 spots available & is first come first serve. Payment must be made in order to reserve your spot.
